710758f-a.text:
1. West Shore Railroad freight yards, Twelfth Avenue, east side, between 36th and 37th Streets. August 30, 1934. P. L. Sperr.

2. The same, slightly northward. The street, seen in the foreground is West 37th Street as viewed eastward. Also shown (left) are buildings facing on the north side of West 39th Street. Under construction at the S.W. corner of the afore mentioned street and Eleventh Ave. is the Ventilator Building of the Midtown Hudson Tunnel. December 5, 1936. P. L. Sperr.
